comments: Walker IV (SAS) makes contact with Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) arm as he is gathering the ball.
Bazley (OKC) maintains a legal guarding position during Murray's (SAS) drive to the rim.
Sarr (OKC) is set in Johnson's (SAS) path and delivers marginal contact during the screen attempt.
Johnson (SAS) reaches around Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) body and cleanly dislodges the ball on the drive.
Poeltl (SAS) firms up and delivers marginal contact to Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) during the screen.
Johnson (SAS) briefly hooks Pokusevski's (OKC) arm at the start of his drive, the contact is marginal and did not affect Pokusevski's ability to defend the play.
Sarr (OKC) delivers marginal body contact to Poeltl's (SAS) body during his shot attempt near the rim.
Poeltl (SAS) gets beat to the spot and delivers marginal body contact to Bazley (OKC) at the start of his drive.

Johnson (SAS) makes incidental contact with Sarr's (OKC) head while tracking the loose ball in the post. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Poeltl (SAS) legally blocks Bazley's (OKC) shot attempt at the rim.
While defending the shot at the rim, Pokusevski (OKC) makes marginal contact with Johnson's (SAS) body and clean contact with the ball.
Murray (SAS) accidentally trips on Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) foot as he goes for the rebound.
Sarr (OKC) extends both arms into Poeltl's (SAS) back and delivers marginal contact during the rebound attempt.
Pokusevski (OKC) legally contests Murray's (SAS) shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release of the shot is considered incidental.
Poeltl (SAS) slightly extends his forearm into Sarr's (OKC) body during the rebound attempt, the contact is marginal and did not affect Sarr's ability to rebound the ball.
Johnson (SAS) contacts the ball after it has made contact with the backboard and it still has an opportunity to score.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) makes marginal contact to Walker IV's (SAS) arm at the start of his drive towards the rim.
Maledon (OKC) makes incidental contact with Primo (SAS) that does not affect his FOM.
Murray (SAS) briefly holds Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) during the screen attempt, the contact is marginal and did not affect Gilgeous-Alexander's FOM.
